visual clarity, we have chosen a digraph which is an <em>oriented
graph</em>, i.e., for each distinct pair <m>x,y</m> of vertices, the graph
contains at most one of the two possible directed edges <m>(x,y)</m> and
<m>(y,x)</m>.
</p>
